OLD: helpers_generate_id(prefix)
NEW: helpers_generate_id(prefix, length)  — where "length" controls the zero-padded digit count

In AILang (no default parameters): every call site must be updated to pass the length argument.
Update the function definition and all call sites.

RULES:
1. Update the function definition in helpers.ail (AILang) / core/helpers.py (Python).
2. For AILang: update helpers_generate_id to accept (idPrefix, idLength). The idLength controls padding digits in helpers_pad_number. Default behavior (length=4) for backward compatibility is NOT possible in AILang — all call sites must be updated.
3. For Python: add the parameter with a default (length=4) so existing call sites still work.
4. Do NOT change any behavior other than the signature.
5. The full test suite must pass (38/38).
